2.10	Rudyard,_Staffordshire	Rudyard, Staffordshire	The Rudyard Lake was built in 1797 by the engineer John Rennie, for the Trent and Mersey Canal company, to provide water for the Caldon Canal. The Rudyard Lake Steam Railway operates steam trains along a one and a half mile track along the eastern side of the lake. The western shore is part of the Staffordshire Way, a long distance footpath.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/98/Reflectionrudyard.jpg/200px-Reflectionrudyard.jpg
